# Mobile on-device verification

**RN-Web Storybook is not a substitute for Android.** Merge gates may use RN-Web + test-runner; **release** requires on-device validation for native-affecting changes.

## Trust on-device, not the browser

Verify on a **real device or emulator** (not RN-Web alone) when touching:

- `react-native-reanimated`, `react-native-gesture-handler`, `react-native-keyboard-controller`
- Lists: `FlatList`, `FlashList`, large scroll performance
- `react-native-track-player`, audio focus, notifications
- `react-native-saf-x`, file pickers
- Fonts (`react-native-vector-icons`), safe area, TalkBack order, haptics, AMOLED appearance

## Gates (summary)

- **Merge:** RN-Web + desktop web Storybook test-runner + a11y addon (automated first — does not replace TalkBack / focus-order manual checks).
- **Release:** QA runs on-device Storybook or app build + checklist (`specs/review-checklists/design-system-on-device.md` when added) for every DS surface touched in the release.

## Platform

- **Android only** — no iOS Storybook or iOS-driven layout rules (see `specs/architecture/platform-targets.md`).
